modules.description: This module configures and initializes a trace collector for capturing execution traces. It provides `collector` to retrieve the trace collector instance and `setup` to install it. Use this module to enable tracing in applications for debugging or performance analysis.

This module tracks execution spans with hierarchical timing, annotations, and metadata for profiling. It supports operations to enter and exit spans, attach text or numeric values, set colors, and name threads, all tied to specific source locations. Concrete use cases include instrumenting functions to visualize execution flow in Tracy's UI, adding contextual logs to spans, and plotting numerical metrics over time.
